  "prompt": "How do people know if they have diabetes?",
  "response": "People can identify potential diabetes symptoms through several methods:\n\n1. Common symptoms:\n- Frequent urination\n- Excessive thirst\n- Unexplained weight loss\n- Blurred vision\n- Slow-healing wounds\n- Fatigue\n- Increased hunger\n\n2. Medical tests:\n- Fasting blood glucose test\n- Hemoglobin A1C test\n- Oral glucose tolerance test\n- Random blood sugar test\n\n3. Risk factors:\n- Family history of diabetes\n- Being overweight\n- Age over 45\n- Physical inactivity\n- High blood pressure\n- High cholesterol\n\n4. Professional diagnosis:\n- Consulting a healthcare provider\n- Discussing symptoms and risk factors\n- Undergoing recommended medical tests\n\n5. At-home monitoring:\n- Using blood glucose meters\n- Tracking symptoms\n- Regular health check-ups\n\nIf someone experiences multiple symptoms or has risk factors, they should consult a healthcare professional for proper evaluation and potential diagnosis. Early detection and management are crucial for preventing complications.",
